{{Infobox character | name = Aimi Eguchi | series = Corporate promotion | image = Aimi Eguchi.jpg | image_size = 280px | caption = Aimi Eguchi as she appears in the Ezaki Glico commercial | first = June 2011 | last = | creator = [[Ezaki Glico]] | portrayer = | voice = [[AKB48#Kenkyusei|Yukari Sasaki]] | lbl21 = Birth date | data21 = {{birth date|1995|2|11}} | alias = | species = | gender = [[Female]] | occupation = [[Japanese idol]] | nationality = Japan }} {{nihongo|'''Aimi Eguchi'''|江口 愛実|Eguchi Aimi}} is a fictional [[Japanese idol]]. She is a [[Computer-generated imagery|CGI]] composite of various features of seven existing (now former) members of the theater/idol group [[AKB48]].<ref name=CNA>[http://www.channelnewsasia.com/stories/entertainment/view/1136166/1/.html AKB 48 newest member Aimi Eguchi is a 'virtual idol'] channelnewsasia.com, 20 June 2011</ref>
Eguchi was announced as the group's newest member in June 2011. According to an official profile she was 16 years old, born on February 11, 1995, and from [[Saitama, Saitama|Saitama]], north of [[Tokyo]]. She was featured in the Japanese magazine ''[[Weekly Playboy]]'', and appeared in a television commercial for the confectionery company, [[Ezaki Glico]]. Suspicions arose amongst AKB48 fans and on June 19, 2011, Glico finally admitted that Eguchi was a fake created by the company, disappointing many fans.<ref>[http://singularityhub.com/2011/06/22/new-japanese-pop-idol-shocks-fans-with-news%E2%80%93shes-not-real-video/ New Japanese Pop Idol Shocks Fans With News–She’s Not Real] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110626184544/http://singularityhub.com/2011/06/22/new-japanese-pop-idol-shocks-fans-with-news%E2%80%93shes-not-real-video/ |date=2011-06-26 }} Singularity Hub, 22 June 2011</ref><ref>[http://www.time.com/time/world/article/0,8599,2079769,00.html Japanese Scientists Build a Perfect (and Fake) Pop Star] TIME.com, 24 June 2011</ref> {{As of|2013|5}}, she is no longer listed on the official website as a trainee.<ref name="akb48members">{{cite web|url=http://www.akb48.co.jp/about/members/|title=AKB48公式サイト｜メンバー情報 (AKB48 Official Site - Member List) |language=Japanese| work = AKB48 Official Website | accessdate = May 9, 2013}} - list is subject to change from graduations and transfers</ref><ref>{{cite web|date = June 25, 2013 |url=http://nihongogo.com/2013/06/aimi-eguchi-officially-graduates-from-akb48/ |title=Aimi Eguchi "officially" graduates from AKB48 |publisher=Nihongogo |accessdate=2013-08-27}}</ref>
