'''''KFOG KaBoom''''' was an annual outdoor concert held by [[KFOG]] in [[San Francisco]] and which occurred in May from 1994 to 2010. It was followed by a fireworks show<ref>{{Cite web | title =KFOG KaBoom! | publisher =Teevan Productions | url =http://teevanproductions.com/kfog.html | accessdate =August 31, 2011 }}</ref><ref>[https://archive.org/search.php?query=KFOG%20kaboom%20AND%20collection%3Aopensource_movies Internet Archive: Open Source Movies]</ref> synchronized to a soundtrack broadcast by the station. The extravagant fireworks display drew over 350,000 people.<ref>[http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/blogs/culture/detail?blogid=3&entry_id=4239 350,000 people and KFOG KaBoom]</ref> In 2007, KaBoom began charging admission due to rising costs.<ref>[http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/blogs/nwzchik/detail?blogid=32&entry_id=16469 "this is the first year the station is charging" Suzanne Herel @ sfgate.com]</ref>
Through 1998, the event was known as the ''Sky Concert'', but was renamed in 1999.<ref>http://www.epa.gov/fedrgstr/EPA-IMPACT/1999/July/Day-21/i18486.htm</ref> Reportedly, this was due to the name being too generic {{Citation needed|date=May 2010}} and may conflict with Keilwerth S.K.Y. Concert Saxophones.{{Citation needed|date=May 2010}}
In 2010, the [[Port of San Francisco]] informed KFOG that Piers 30/32 in downtown San Francisco could no longer support the heavy equipment and vehicles necessary to produce large events.<ref name="kaboom">http://www.kfog.com/Pages/KFOGKaBoom2010.aspx</ref> In May of that same year, KaBoom was moved from the pier location to the parking lot of [[Candlestick Park]].
In the spring of 2011, KFOG announced that a proper venue for the show could not be found, and that KaBoom for 2011 was cancelled. No announcement has since been made for KaBoom since 2012.<ref>[http://www.kfog.com KFOG 104.5/97.7 FM: World Class Rock|accessdate=May 11, 2011]</ref>
'''Previous artists (in order of appearance):'''
*1994 (Sky Concert) - [[The Subdudes]], [[NRBQ]] *1995 (Sky Concert) - [[Timbuk3]], [[The Freddy Jones Band]]<ref>https://groups.google.com/group/ba.music/browse_thread/thread/4164243c8caf86b/572b466455d02528</ref> *1996 (Sky Concert) - [[The Odds]], [[Robben Ford]] and The Blue Line *1997 (Sky Concert) - The Odds, [[Wilco]], [[Keb' Mo']]<ref>http://search.sfweekly.com/1997-05-28/music/the-house-of-tudor/</ref> *1998 (Sky Concert) - [[Pete Droge]], The Scott Thomas Ban, [[Roomful of Blues]] *1999 - [[Wes Cunningham]], The Boneshakers, Wilco *2000 - [[Pat McGee Band]], [[Shannon Curfman]], [[Kenny Wayne Shepherd]] *2001 - [[Old 97's]], [[Mother Hips]], [[Blues Traveler]]<ref>http://alex.pecanbiz.com/KFOG_SF_May01/sanfran.html</ref> *2002 - [[Zero 7]], [[Robert Bradley's Blackwater Surprise]], [[Boz Scaggs]]<ref>{{cite news| url=https://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9E0DEFD9153AF934A35757C0A9649C8B63 | work=The New York Times | first=Christopher | last=Hall | title=WHAT'S DOING IN; San Francisco | date=April 7, 2002}}</ref> *2003 - [[Keller Williams]], [[Nickel Creek]], [[Susan Tedeschi]], [[Steve Winwood]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kfog.com/kaboom/2003.asp |accessdate=December 29, 2007 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080820062427/http://www.kfog.com/kaboom/2003.asp |archivedate=August 20, 2008 }}</ref> *2004 - [[Train (band)|Train]], [[The Waifs]], [[Robert Randolph & the Family Band]]<ref>http://www.kfog.com/kaboom/2004.asp {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080820062136/http://www.kfog.com/kaboom/2004.asp |date=August 20, 2008 }}</ref> *2005 - [[John Butler Trio]], [[Kathleen Edwards]], [[The Wallflowers|Wallflowers]]<ref>http://www.kfog.com/kaboom/2005.asp {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070902134405/http://www.kfog.com/kaboom/2005.asp |date=September 2, 2007 }}</ref> *2006 - [[Jackie Greene]], [[KT Tunstall]], [[Los Lonely Boys]]<ref>http://www.kfog.com/kaboom/2006.asp {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080514033038/http://www.kfog.com/kaboom/2006.asp |date=May 14, 2008 }}</ref> *2007 - [[Ozomatli]], [[Guster]], Kenny Wayne Shepherd *2008 - [[Collective Soul]], [[Los Lobos]], [[Matt Nathanson]] *2009 - [[Chuck Prophet]], [[Los Lonely Boys]], [[Susan Tedeschi]]<ref>https://archive.is/20120708220509/https://webcache.googleusercontent.com/search?q=cache:www.kfog.com/Pages/KFOGKaBoom2009.aspx</ref> *2010 - [[Melissa Etheridge]], [[John Butler Trio]], [[Grace Potter and the Nocturnals]]<ref name="kaboom" />
