{{Italic title}} {{use dmy dates|date=August 2017}} {{Infobox concert | concert_name = ''Modena Park 2017'' | image = | caption = | artist = [[Vasco Rossi]] | type = Rock | date = {{date|2017-07-01}} | venue = [[Modena]], [[Italy]] | tour = | album = <!-- or | albums = --> | number_of_shows = 1 | duration = 3:38:36 | support_act = <!-- or | support_acts = --> | attendance = 225,173 | gross = €12,000,000 | website = | last_concert = | this_concert = | next_concert = }}
'''''Modena Park 2017''''' was a concert performed by Italian rock singer [[Vasco Rossi]] on 1 July 2017 in [[Modena]], Italy, to celebrate his 40 years of musical activity. Held at [[Modena Autodrome|Enzo Ferrari Park]], the event broke the [[world record]] for the most successful ticketed concert,<ref> *{{cite news|url=http://www.bestunion.it/concert-celebration-event-for-vasco-rossis-40-year-long-career-a-world-record-sold-out/?lang=en|title=Concert-celebration event for Vasco Rossi's 40-year-long career: A world-record sold out (press release) |newspaper=[[Il Sole 24 Ore]] |date=2017-06-23 |accessdate=2017-07-07 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170826124647/http://www.bestunion.it/concert-celebration-event-for-vasco-rossis-40-year-long-career-a-world-record-sold-out/?lang=en|archivedate=26 August 2017|df=dmy-all}} *{{citeweb|url=http://www.theticketingbusiness.com/2017/06/29/vasco-rossi-break-concert-attendance-world-record|title=Vasco Rossi to break concert attendance WORLD RECORD|date=29 June 2017|publisher=The Ticketing Business|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170818185541/http://www.theticketingbusiness.com/2017/06/29/vasco-rossi-break-concert-attendance-world-record/|archivedate=18 August 2017|df=dmy-all}} *{{citeweb|url=https://www.pollstar.com/article/rossi-sets-record-in-italy-132226|title=Rossi sets record in Italy|last=Gottfried|first=Gideon|date=29 June 2017|publisher=Pollstar|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170826124646/https://www.pollstar.com/article/rossi-sets-record-in-italy-132226|archivedate=26 August 2017|df=dmy-all}} *{{it icon}} {{cite news|title=Vasco Rossi, è record mondiale, venduti 220.000 biglietti biglietti per il concerto di Modena |newspaper=[[La Repubblica]] |date=2017-05-24 |url=http://www.repubblica.it/spettacoli/people/2017/05/24/news/vasco_rossi_e_record_mondiale_venduti_220_000_biglietti_per_il_concerto_di_modena-166275197/|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170702221846/http://www.repubblica.it/spettacoli/people/2017/05/24/news/vasco_rossi_e_record_mondiale_venduti_220_000_biglietti_per_il_concerto_di_modena-166275197/|archivedate=2 July 2017|df=dmy-all}} </ref> with a total of 225,173 tickets sold (including 5,000 free tickets).<ref>{{it icon}} {{Cite news|title=Modena Park, Vasco oltre il sold out: c'erano prenotazioni per altri 160mila biglietti|magazine=Dire|date=2017-07-07 |url=http://www.dire.it/07-07-2017/132470-modena-park-vasco-oltre-sold-out-cerano-prenotazioni-altri-160mila-biglietti/|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170707165005/http://www.dire.it/07-07-2017/132470-modena-park-vasco-oltre-sold-out-cerano-prenotazioni-altri-160mila-biglietti/|archivedate=7 July 2017|df=dmy-all}}</ref>
==History== [[File:Vasco o.jpg|thumb|upright|[[Vasco Rossi]] in 2016]] The last concert performed by Vasco in Modena dates back to 22 September 2001 during the [[Festa de l'Unità|Festa nazionale de l'Unità]], on his ''Stupido Hotel'' tour.<ref>{{it icon}} {{Cite news |last=Marini |first=Andrea |title="Festeggio i miei 40 anni di live con un concerto a Modena Park" |newspaper=Gazzetta di Modena |date=2016-04-21 |url=http://gazzettadimodena.gelocal.it/modena/cronaca/2016/04/21/news/festeggio-i-miei-40-anni-di-live-con-un-concerto-a-modena-park-1.13336568 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170803130239/http://gazzettadimodena.gelocal.it/modena/cronaca/2016/04/21/news/festeggio-i-miei-40-anni-di-live-con-un-concerto-a-modena-park-1.13336568 |archivedate=3 August 2017|df=dmy-all}}</ref>
On 19 April 2016, Vasco announced the organization of a concert in Modena, the city where he began his 40-year career as a DJ and singer. Initially, the event was to be called ''Modena... Modena park tutto ritorna'' (Modena... Modena Park all is back), in reference to lyrics of his song ''Colpa d'Alfredo'' (''Alfredo's fault''), in which a girl asks Vasco, "Mi puoi portare a casa questa sera? Abito fuori Modena, Modena park" ("Can you bring me home tonight? I'm living out of Modena... Modena Park"), but then she goes out with another man "who does not even speak Italian well, but&nbsp;– you see – he is well understood whenever he wants".<ref>{{it icon}} {{Cite news|title=Vasco Rossi: 'Luglio 2017: Modena Park un grande evento a Modena per i miei 40 anni di palco'|newspaper=Gazzetta di Modena|date=2016-04-19 |5=|url=http://gazzettadimodena.gelocal.it/tempo-libero/2016/04/19/news/incontri-d-autore-intervista-a-vasco-rossi-la-diretta-dall-auditorium-1.13325813|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170805015011/http://gazzettadimodena.gelocal.it/tempo-libero/2016/04/19/news/incontri-d-autore-intervista-a-vasco-rossi-la-diretta-dall-auditorium-1.13325813|archivedate=5 August 2017|df=dmy-all}}</ref>
On 25 January 2017 ticket sales were opened to fan club members, who bought 33,112 tickets in 48 hours, and then two days later to the general public. On 27 January alone 150,000 tickets were sold in 10 hours,<ref>{{it icon}} {{Cite news|title=Vasco Rossi live a Modena Park: venduti 180mila biglietti|newspaper=Gazzetta di Modena |date=2017-01-27 |url=http://gazzettadimodena.gelocal.it/modena/cronaca/2017/01/27/news/vasco-modena-park-venduti-180mila-biglietti-1.14780712 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170803130554/http://gazzettadimodena.gelocal.it/modena/cronaca/2017/01/27/news/vasco-modena-park-venduti-180mila-biglietti-1.14780712|archivedate=3 August 2017|df=dmy-all}}</ref> and at 8:13&nbsp;PM Vasco announced on Twitter that he "Pulverized the European record!"<ref>{{Twitter|id=vascorossi|name=Vasco Rossi|tweetid=825059125688164354|title=#ModenaPark 180000 Polverizzato record europeo!|date=2017-01-27}}</ref> The final block of 25,000 tickets was put on sale on 23 May, selling out within three hours.{{cn|date=September 2017}}
==Program== The concert began at 9:00&nbsp;PM and included 40 songs by Vasco (one for each year of his career). The event ended after three and a half hours and concluded with the 1979 single ''Albachiara'' and a fireworks show.<ref>{{it icon}} {{cite news|last=Marini |first=Andrea |title=Ciao! Benvenuti nella leggenda |newspaper=Gazzetta di Modena |date=2 July 2017 |page=2}}</ref>
Program:<ref>{{it icon}} {{cite news|title=Questa è una festa gioiosa, noi non abbiamo paura |newspaper=Gazzetta di Modena |date=2017-07-02 |page=3}}</ref> {{div col|colwidth=30em}} * Opening intro: ''[[Also sprach Zarathustra (Strauss)|Also sprach Zarathustra]]'' by [[Richard Strauss]] * ''Colpa d'Alfredo'' * ''Alibi'' * ''Blasco Rossi'' * ''Bollicine'' * ''Ogni volta'' * ''Anima fragile'' (with Gaetano Curreri) * ''Jenny'' * ''Silvia'' * ''La nostra relazione'' * ''Splendida giornata'' * ''Ieri ho sgozzato mio figlio'' * Rock medley: ''Delusa'', ''T'immagini'', ''Mi piaci perché'', ''Gioca con me'', ''Stasera!,'' ''Sono ancora in coma'', ''Rock'n'roll Show'' * ''Ultimo domicilio conosciuto'' (with Maurizio Solieri) * ''Vivere una favola'' * ''Non mi va'' * ''Cosa vuoi da me'' * ''Siamo soli'' * ''Come nelle favole'' * ''Vivere'' * ''Sono innocente ma...'' * ''Rewind'' * ''Liberi liberi'' * ''Interludio 2017'' (with Andrea Braido) * ''Ed il tempo crea eroi'' * Acoustic medley: ''Una canzone per te'', ''L'una per te'', ''Ridere di te'', ''Va bene, va bene così'' * ''Senza parole'' * ''...stupendo'' * ''Gli spari sopra'' * ''Sballi ravvicinati del terzo tipo'' * ''C'è chi dice no'' * ''Un mondo migliore'' * ''I soliti'' * ''Sally'' * ''Un senso'' * ''Siamo solo noi'' * Band presentation by Diego Spagnoli * ''Vita spericolata'' * ''Canzone'' – dedicated to guitarist Massimo Riva (1963–1999) * ''Albachiara'' (with Andrea Braido, Gaetano Curreri, and Maurizio Solieri) * Closing credits: ''Die for Metal'' by [[Manowar]] {{div col end}}
==Band== {{div col|colwidth=30em}} * [[Vasco Rossi]] – vocals<ref name="Mag 2017">{{it icon}} {{cite web | title=Vasco Rossi dopo Modena Park è "Senza parole": anteprima mondiale | website=Sky Mag | date=4 September 2017 | url=http://mag.sky.it/musica/2017/09/04/vasco-rossi-modena-park-senza-parole-anteprima.html | accessdate=15 September 2017}}</ref> * Stef Burns – electric guitar<ref name=RadioItalia>{{cite web |title=VASCO ROSSI: VASCO MODENA PARK FA “LA STORIA” DAVANTI A 220MILA FAN |website=Radio Italia |date=2017-07-02 |url=http://www.radioitalia.it/news/vasco_rossi/evento/15003_vasco_rossi_vasco_modena_park_fa_%E2%80%9Cla_storia%E2%80%9D_davanti_a_220mila_fan.php}}</ref> * Claudio Golinelli – bass guitar<ref name=RadioItalia/> * Andrea Innesto – choir<ref name=RadioItalia/> * [[Matt Laug]] – drums<ref name=RadioItalia/> * Clara Moroni – choir<ref name=RadioItalia/> * Frank Nemola – trumpet, keyboard<ref name=RadioItalia/> * Vince Pastano – guitar<ref name=RadioItalia/> * Alberto Rocchetti – keyboard * Diego Spagnoli – band presenter<ref name=RadioItalia/> * Andrea Braido – guitar (guest)<ref name=RadioItalia/> * Gaetano Curreri – piano (guest)<ref name=RadioItalia/> * Maurizio Solieri – guitar (guest)<ref name=RadioItalia/> {{div col end}}
==Staging== [[File:Vigili del fuoco al concerto di Vasco Rossi al Modena Park.jpg|300px|thumb|left|A moment of the concert]] The stage at Enzo Ferrari park was {{convert|165|m}} long and stood {{convert|8|m}} off the ground. It featured five large video screens with a total area of {{convert|1500|m²}}. Four of these were set on tracks, so that they could move sideways depending on the video [[scenography]] required during each song. The remaining four screens, two per side, were installed within PIT 3. Special effects were produced by 2,100 light points and 140 lasers. Transportation of all the staging equipment required a total of 136 semi-trailer trucks.<ref>{{it icon}} {{cite news |last=Zuffi |first=Danilo |title=Un impianto avvenieristico per vivere insieme lo show |newspaper=Gazzetta di Modena |date=29 June 2017 |page=V}}</ref><ref>{{{it icon}} {{cite news |last=Marini |first=Andrea |title=Palco come scalo merci: nei container la Vasco-story |newspaper=Gazzetta di Modena |date=29 June 2017 |page=VII}}</ref>
The sound was played through a 750,000-watt [[L-Acoustics]] audio system consisting of 900 speaker modules connected by {{convert|100|km}} of [[fiber optic cables]], with 29 sound towers to allow all 230,000 viewers along a {{convert|400|m|adj=on}}-long lawn to listen without return or echo effects. According to production staff, one [[Watt#Megawatt|megawatt]] of energy was consumed during the concert. The two main towers located in front of the stage, each containing 80 speaker modules, were suspended using two-ton cranes for each tower.<ref>{{it icon}} {{Cite news |title=Vasco canta a 750 mila watt, con 29 torri diffusione e 100 km di cavi |last=Pagliarini |first=Enrico |newspaper=Il Sole 24 Ore |date=1 July 2017 |url=http://mobile.ilsole24ore.com/solemobile/main/art/cultura/2017-07-01/vasco-canta-750-mila-watt-29-torri-diffusione-e-100-km-cavi-093534.shtml |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170804214324/http://mobile.ilsole24ore.com/solemobile/main/art/cultura/2017-07-01/vasco-canta-750-mila-watt-29-torri-diffusione-e-100-km-cavi-093534.shtml |archivedate=4 August 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>
==Audience== [[File:Modena Park 2017 veduta elicottero.jpg|300px|thumb|right|Audience at ''Modena Park 2017'']] Over 220,000 tickets to the concert were sold, beating the previous world record of 198,000 paying attendees at the [[A-ha|a-Ha]] concert at the [[Rock in Rio|Rock in Rio 2]] festival on 26 January 1991.<ref>{{cite news |last=Weissberg |first=Brad |title=Italy To Host Biggest Ticketed Concert Ever: 220,000 tickets sold for Italian star Vasco Rossi Concert |website=Venues Now |date=28 June 2017|url=http://www.venuesnow.com/news/detail/italy-hosts-biggest-ticketed-concert-ever |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170804220356/http://www.venuestoday.com/news/detail/italy-hosts-biggest-ticketed-concert-ever |archivedate=4 August 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> The arena was split into three areas: Pits 1 and 2 accommodated 30,000 attendees each, and Pit 3 seated the remainder. The areas were marked with different colours (red, blue, and green), and with different ticket prices (€75, €65, and €50, pre-sale fees and commissions excluded). The total gross for the concert was about €12 million<ref>{{it icon}} {{cite news |last=Prisco |first=Francesco |title=Vasco a Modena per il concerto con più paganti di sempre: incasso di 12 milioni |newspaper=Il Sole 24 Ore |date=2017-05-23 |url=http://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/cultura/2017-05-23/vasco-modena-il-concerto-piu-paganti-sempre-incasso-12-milioni-143017.shtml |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170804214542/http://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/cultura/2017-05-23/vasco-modena-il-concerto-piu-paganti-sempre-incasso-12-milioni-143017.shtml |archivedate=4 August 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> (USD$13.7 million), while the economic impact on the city was estimated at €6 million.<ref>{{it icon}} {{Cite news |title=Modena Park, un indotto da sei milioni di euro |newspaper=Gazzetta di Modena |date=2017-06-28 |url=http://gazzettadimodena.gelocal.it/modena/cronaca/2017/06/28/news/modena-park-un-indotto-da-sei-milioni-di-euro-1.15547679 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170628174141/http://gazzettadimodena.gelocal.it/modena/cronaca/2017/06/28/news/modena-park-un-indotto-da-sei-milioni-di-euro-1.15547679 |archivedate=28 June 2017|df=dmy-all}}</ref>
Gate opening was initially scheduled for 9:00&nbsp;AM on 1 July. However, considering the crowd that had arrived on the previous day, the police ordered the gates opened at 9:00&nbsp;PM on 30 June, twenty-four hours before the concert began.<ref>{{it icon}} {{cite news |last=Berti |first=Davide |title=La marea dei fan: il lungo serpentone umano dove conta solo "esserci" tra birre, acqua e contapassi |newspaper=Gazzetta di Modena |date=2 July 2017 |page=8}}</ref> One fan from [[Pordenone]] began camping in Modena on 29 May, a full month prior, in order to be the first person to enter the park.<ref>{{it icon}} {{Cite news|title=Vasco Rossi, il record di Steve: accampato da 30 giorni al Modena Park |agency=[[Adnkronos]]|date=2017-06-30 |url=http://www.adnkronos.com/intrattenimento/spettacolo/2017/06/30/vasco-rossi-record-steve-accampato-giorni-modena-park_eDCQgbnzfxGJo1vvXEs5tL.html |deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170630180248/http://www.adnkronos.com/intrattenimento/spettacolo/2017/06/30/vasco-rossi-record-steve-accampato-giorni-modena-park_eDCQgbnzfxGJo1vvXEs5tL.html |archivedate=30 June 2017 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>
==Logistics== The national railroad company [[Trenitalia]] scheduled three special long-distance trains to depart from [[Rome]], [[Turin]]/[[Milan]], and [[Venice]] for the [[Modena railway station]]. After the concert, more than 35 trains were scheduled to depart. It was estimated that about 35,000 people reached Modena by train.<ref>{{it icon}} {{Cite news |title=Vasco Modena Park, treni quasi esauriti. E i pullman saranno 900|newspaper=Gazzetta di Modena |date=2017-06-24 |url=http://gazzettadimodena.gelocal.it/modena/cronaca/2017/06/24/news/in-auto-o-treno-al-vasco-modena-park-ecco-consigli-e-orari-1.15530888 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170712092245/http://gazzettadimodena.gelocal.it/modena/cronaca/2017/06/24/news/in-auto-o-treno-al-vasco-modena-park-ecco-consigli-e-orari-1.15530888 |archivedate=12 July 2017|df=dmy-all}}</ref>
==Broadcasting== The concert was broadcast live under the title ''Vasco Modena Park 01.07.17 – Live''. Directed by Giuseppe Domingo Romano credited as Pepsy Romanoff,<ref>{{it icon}} {{cite news |title=Vasco Rossi, Modena Park arriva al cinema |date=2017-10-26 |magazine=[[Rolling Stone#International editions|Rolling Stone Italia]] |url=https://www.rollingstone.it/musica/news-musica/vasco-rossi-modena-park-arriva-al-cinema/388671/|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181106081620/https://www.rollingstone.it/musica/news-musica/vasco-rossi-modena-park-arriva-al-cinema/388671/|archivedate=6 November 2018|df=dmy-all}}</ref> it was shown in 197 movie theaters in Italy and three sports venues ([[Genoa]], [[Padua]], and [[Rome]]). The concert was followed by official radio re-broadcasts on [[Radio Dimensione Suono]] and [[Radio Italia Solo Musica Italiana|Radio Italia]] (at the national level), and Radio Bruno (at the local level). National television company [[RAI]], unable to acquire the broadcasting rights for all the songs, aired on [[Eurovision (network)|Eurovision]] on [[Rai 1]] and [[Rai 1|Rai 1 HD]] the special program ''La notte di Vasco'' ("Vasco's night") by [[Paolo Bonolis]], in addition to the programming of [[Rai Radio 2]].<ref name=davidemaggio.it/>
